  <Section title="FulGore" emoji="ü¶ñ">
    <p>
      You may remember FulGore from the game's release. It makes a comeback return in TU4 now that
      we can fit Lord's Soul.
    </p>

    <p>
      We use 2 Transcended Fulgur Anjanath pieces to activate <strong>Second Wind</strong>. This
      grants a secondary stamina gauge, allowing you to execute stamina-heavy moves (like Dash
      Attack, Grand Retribution Thrust, or hops) without depleting your main bar. This prevents
      Maximum Might from deactivating, potentially allowing you to match or even exceed Gorcherer's
      damage output.
    </p>

    <p>
      However, this set is a bit harder to execute. You need to already be quite good at managing
      stamina to make good use of the tiny extra stamina bar. If you struggle with stamina, the
      passive damage from Scorcherer is simply more reliable. On the other hand, if your management
      is too good, you may not need the safety net of Second Wind to begin with.
    </p>

    <p>
      Ultimately, I believe FulGore shines if you have good monster knowledge and can play
      aggressively with stamina-draining moves (like GRT), whereas Gorcherer remains the simpler,
      more general option.
    </p>

